fields.name: Large Medkit
fields.preview_text: The large medkit is a seldom used 'upgrade' to the medical syringe. It can regenerate a player to full health over time, but provides no instant health bonus like the syringes it is crafted from.
fields.detail_text:
The large medkit is a seldom used 'upgrade' to the medical syringe. It can regenerate a player to full health over time, but provides no instant health bonus like the syringes it is crafted from.

This item is rarely used in combat as any incoming damage will stop the healing process. Many players use it to heal after failing radtown jumping puzzles as they are mainly found in radtowns.

fields.name: Medical Syringe
fields.preview_text: The medical syringe is the go-to medical solution for combat in game. Providing a good boost of health instantly with a decent regeneration afterwards. It's quick use and simplicity makes it a fan fav
fields.detail_text: The medical syringe is the go-to medical solution for combat in game. Providing a good boost of health instantly with a decent regeneration afterwards. It's quick use and simplicity makes it a fan favorite in combat.

fields.name: Assault Rifle
fields.preview_text: The Assault Rifle is an accurate, powerful, and fully automatic rifle that fires 5.56 rifle rounds. It has a moderate rate of fire which allows for proficiency at close to medium range.
fields.detail_text:
The Assault Rifle is an accurate, powerful, and fully automatic rifle that fires 5.56 rifle rounds. It has a moderate rate of fire which allows for proficiency at close to medium range.

Strong recoil makes it more difficult to fire in full-auto at long range, but experienced users may be able to control it more effectively.

The Assault Rifle is generally used as an end-game multipurpose weapon, able to take fights at any range.

fields.name: Bandana Mask
fields.preview_text: Cheap facial attire compatible with most head slots that wouldn't otherwise obscure it.
fields.detail_text: Cheap facial attire compatible with most head slots that wouldn't otherwise obscure it.

fields.name: Bone Armor
fields.preview_text: Respectable projectile and melee resistance has promoted bone armor to a heightened status within the primitive era.
fields.detail_text:
Respectable projectile and melee resistance has promoted bone armor to a heightened status within the primitive era.

Its slot efficiency is often exploited during helicopter patrols.

fields.name: Bone Helmet
fields.preview_text: Second only to the wolf headdress in primitive headwear, the bone helmet is a welcome sink for bone frags until metal can take its place.
fields.detail_text: Second only to the wolf headdress in primitive headwear, the bone helmet is a welcome sink for bone frags until metal can take its place.

fields.name: Coffee Can Helmet
fields.preview_text: The coffee can helmet is a face protector that is one tier below the metal facemask, it offers good protection against physical damage to the head and costs less to craft than its older and better...
fields.detail_text: The coffee can helmet is a face protector that is one tier below the metal facemask, it offers good protection against physical damage to the head and costs less to craft than its older and better brother, the metal facemask.

fields.name: Hazmat Suit
fields.preview_text: The Hazmat Suit allows one to safely travel through irradiated zones, signified by Geiger counter style ticking. When the Suit is equipped, the wearer will be protected from most radioactive zones.
fields.detail_text:
The Hazmat Suit allows one to safely travel through irradiated zones, signified by Geiger counter style ticking. When the Suit is equipped, the wearer will be protected from most radioactive zones

It does not provide full protection in certain areas, such as in the main building at the Launch Site, or the broken cooling tower at the Nuclear Power Plant.

The main use of the Suit is to travel into irradiated zones, as its protective ability in combat is inferior to mid-tier equipment. However, in a pinch, it is better than being naked, unless one is trying to remain undetected as the bright yellow makes a person stand out against the landscape.

fields.name: Hoodie
fields.preview_text: The hoodie offers the greatest projectile and melee resistance out of all the under armor variants. This superiority is offset by its high research and production cost.
fields.detail_text: The hoodie offers the greatest projectile and melee resistance out of all the under armor variants. This superiority is offset by its high research and production cost.

fields.name: Metal Chest Plate
fields.preview_text: The metal chest plate is a versatile end-game armor used most often when roaming and raiding. Though high quality metal is often stored in abundance due to its limited use, players should begin...
fields.detail_text: The metal chest plate is a versatile end-game armor used most often when roaming and raiding. Though high quality metal is often stored in abundance due to its limited use, players should begin making room for the sewing kits as this period comes into the horizon.

fields.name: Metal Facemask
fields.preview_text: A high-tier protective face mask which somehow protects the entire head. It costs High Quality Metal, making it quite expensive compared to its alternatives, but in return offers the greatest...
fields.detail_text: A high-tier protective face mask which somehow protects the entire head. It costs High Quality Metal, making it quite expensive compared to its alternatives, but in return offers the greatest protection to almost all forms of physical damage in exchange for decreasing cold protection.

fields.name: Road Sign Jacket
fields.preview_text: The road sign jacket has become the staple of mid-game armor due primarily to its worthwhile projectile resistance without necessitating high quality metal.
fields.detail_text: The road sign jacket has become the staple of mid-game armor due primarily to its worthwhile projectile resistance without necessitating high quality metal.

fields.name: Road Sign Kilt
fields.preview_text: The lack of a metal chest plate or jacket equivalent to leg armor allows the road sign kilt a monopoly on both mid and end-game leg armor. Heavy plate pants are all that can surpass it...
fields.detail_text: The lack of a metal chest plate or jacket equivalent to leg armor allows the road sign kilt a monopoly on both mid and end-game leg armor. Heavy plate pants are all that can surpass it statistically, but these are seldom seen outside of airlock brawls due to its movement penalty.

fields.name: Roadsign Gloves
fields.preview_text: Gloves made out of metal offers a good amount of protection to the upper body.
fields.detail_text: Gloves made out of metal offers a good amount of protection to the upper body.
